The paper deals with coding schemes for Private Information Retrieval (PIR) and batch codes, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories. The use of arrays and the focus on the number of columns suggests a connection to Data Structures (cs.DS) and Distributed Computing (cs.DC). Finally, the study of optimal values and explicit constructions may also relate to Computational Complexity (cs.CC).
